Linear Search
Linear Search is a very simple method for finding any element.
We take a  variable and initialized it False.
We traverse the array and check the condition , current element of the array is equal to k or not if it is equal to k than we assign True
and return the it
class Solution {
  public:
    // Function to find element in sorted array
    // arr: input array
    // k: element to be searched
    bool searchInSorted(vector<int>& arr, int k) {

        // Your code here
        int res=false;
        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            if(arr[i]==k){
                res=true;
            }
            
        }
        return res;
    }
};
